Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Fill and boil your #kettle{}.

Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1}(peeled and chopped) into small pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(grated with a garlic press) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{1%drizzle} in a large #ovenproof saucepan{} on medium heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an ovenproof dish before baking.

Once hot, add the @sliced mushrooms{120%g} and stir-fry until golden, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Next, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g} and onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Once the veg has softened, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then stir in the garlic. Cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir in the @risotto rice{175%g} and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the @water{500%ml}(for the risotto) (see pantry for amount), @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and @wild mushroom paste{15%g} to the pan. Stir well to combine.

Bring back to the boil, then pop a #lid{} on the pan (or cover with #foil{}) and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water has been absorbed, ~{20-25%minutes}.

When the risotto is cooked, remove it from the oven and mix in the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and @butter{30%g} (see pantry for amount).

Season to taste with salt and pepper if needed.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the risotto if needed.

Spoon your risotto into #bowls{} and crumble over the @goat's cheese{75%g}.

Top with the @wild rocket{20%g} and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%drizzle} to finish.

Enjoy!